cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the use of genealogy trees and academic lineage in computer science research, which is relevant to several sub-categories. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of scholarly information. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also relevant as it discusses the formation of academic communities and collaborations. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as it discusses the use of visualization tools to analyze academic networks. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as it discusses the social aspects of academic collaborations. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as it discusses the use of visualization tools to aid in academic research.
